Definition: characterized by careless unconcern
Example: the heedless generosity and the spasmodic extravagance of persons used to large fortunes- Edith Wharton; reckless squandering of public funds
Synonyms: noun, attribute, heedlessness, reckless, recklessness, characterized, by, careless, unconcern, the, generosity, and, spasmodic, extravagance, of, persons, used, to, large, fortunes, -, Edith, Wharton, squandering, public, funds
Category: adj.all
